It is impossible to measure exactly 4 liters using only a 6-liter jug and a 12-liter jug. This is because the greatest common divisor (GCD) of the jug sizes (6 and 12) is 6. In water jug problems, you can only measure amounts that are multiples of the GCD of the jug sizes, up to the total capacity. Since 4 is not a multiple of 6, it cannot be measured with these jugs.

All possible states with these jugs result in amounts that are multiples of 6 liters (e.g., 0, 6, 12 liters), and no sequence of filling, emptying, or pouring between the jugs can produce 4 liters.

\boxed{\text{It is not possible}}
